To run the server, enter the following command on the terminal:

node server.js

default port = 41205

# REST API
# List of HTTP requests to test the server

GET http://{hostname}:{port}				-- Returns the index.html showing all the tweets from the given archive json file
GET http://{hostname}:{port}/api/tweets	    		-- Returns (json) all the available tweets from the archive
GET http://{hostname}:{port}/api/tweet?id=		-- Returns (json) all the details about a given tweet
GET http://{hostname}:{port}/api/users			-- Returns (json) all known twitter users included in the archive
GET http://{hostname}:{port}/api/user?id= 		-- Returns (json) detailed profile information about a given twitter user
GET http://{hostname}:{port}/api/extlinks			-- Returns (json) a list of all external links included in tweets from the archive
GET http://{hostname}:{port}/api/location     		-- Returns (json) a list of google map location link pertaining to a user from the archive
